  /* Schematic description:
   *
   * STM32G491RET6 (U1):
   *   PA5-PA7  → SPI1 → ADS122U04 (U2) SCLK/DOUT/DIN
   *   PA10     → ADS122U04 CS
   *   PA11     → ADS122U04 START
   *   PA12     ← ADS122U04 DRDY
   *   PA8      → TIM1_CH1 PWM → MOSFET1 gate (heater 1)
   *   PA9      → TIM1_CH2 PWM → MOSFET2 gate (heater 2)
   *   PB9      → Heater enable (active LOW = cutoff)
   *   PB8      ← TLV3201 safety comparator output
   *   PA2-PA3  → USART2 → ESP32-C3 TX/RX
   *   PB6-PB7  → I2C1 → SH1106 OLED SCL/SDA
   *   PB2-PB5  → SPI2 → microSD SCK/MISO/MOSI/CS
   *   PB10-PB12 ← Buttons A/B/C
   *   PB13-PB14 → LEDs (red/green)
   *   PB15     → ESP32-C3 EN
   *   PC0      ← Battery voltage (ADC2)
   *   PC1      ← DS18B20 OneWire
   *   PC14-PC15 ← TP4056 CHRG/STDBY
   *
   * ADS122U04 (U2):
   *   AIN0/AIN1  ← Sample PT1000 RTD (differential, 4-wire)
   *   AIN2/AIN3  ← Reference PT1000 RTD (differential, 4-wire)
   *   AIN4      ← Heater current sense (via sense resistor + op-amp)
   *   VDD/AVDD  → 3.3V
   *   IDAC      → 250µA excitation for RTDs
   *
   * Heater circuit:
   *   5V boost → MOSFET1 → Kapton heater 50Ω (sample cell)
   *   5V boost → MOSFET2 → Kapton heater 50Ω (reference cell)
   *   Each heater has PT1000 RTD bonded underneath
   *   0.5Ω sense resistor in series for current measurement
   *   TLV3201 comparator monitors pan temp, cuts at 320°C
   *   250°C thermal fuse in series with 5V heater rail
   *
   * Power:
   *   USB-C 5V → TP4056 → 18650 LiPo → BQ25883 boost → 5V heater rail
   *                                    → AP2112 LDO → 3.3V logic
   */

  (sheet_instances
